					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6546880#post-3891441</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6546880/scp-2544#post-3891441</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 30 Jul 2018 15:12:59 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The jargon is a little thick in places, but I enjoyed it. The idea that the thoughts we get in our heads to hurl ourselves off cliffs or what-have-you being caused by an SCP is a cool one that is executed fairly well here. I would have liked to see more focus on examples of how people have embarrassed themselves or otherwise been affected by this, as the human part of this article is where it shines. Not the best introductory article, but for those familiar with the lore this is built on this is a fun read. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
